    "body": "@fjl that's indeed the way it should work except that go-ethereum seems to use several libraries that are not compatible with wasm. Please consider reopening this issue.\r\n\r\nI've been using go-ethereum successfully for a while but the whole compatibility fall apart when I've tried to use the [signer/core](\"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/signer/core\") package as it has dependencies on libraries [0] that use mmap and other low level file locking systems even if I don't use any feature that needs that kind of locking(i.e. I just need to use core.TypedData struct)\r\n\r\nSee for example this https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/23972\r\n\r\n[0] github.com/prometheus/tsdb/fileutil\r\ngithub.com/edsrzf/mmap-go\r\ngithub.com/syndtr/goleveldb",
